# Regression fixture for issue #43: a species initial condition set by a DERIVED
# (ConstantExpression) parameter Rtot = R0. The fitted primary R0 reaches the
# state ONLY through this derived initial condition (R0 is in no rate law). The
# forward-sensitivity seed ∂R(0)/∂R0 must chain through Rtot = R0 (coefficient
# 1); before the fix the derived-parameter IC dropped the seed and the analytic
# ∂R/∂R0 came back 0 instead of the rebuild-FD value 1.
begin parameters
    1 R0     100.0   # Constant
    2 kf     0.5     # Constant
    3 Rtot   R0      # ConstantExpression
end parameters
begin species
    1 R() Rtot
    2 P() 0.0
end species
begin reactions
    1 1 2 kf   #_R_decay
end reactions
begin groups
    1 R_tot 1
    2 P_tot 2
end groups
